= Excellence (Al-Iḥsān) 



== Definition of Al-Iḥsān:

 • Linguistically: It is the opposite of wrongdoing.
 
 • In Islām: It is being mindful of Allāh in both private and public.



== Pillars of Al-Iḥsān:

 *It has one pillar:*
 
“That you worship Allāh as if you see Him; and if you do not see Him, [know that] He sees you.”



== Categories of Al-Iḥsān:

It is divided into two categories:

*1. Excellence toward creation:*

This is shown through four means:

- Wealth (i.e helping with one ones wealth & property)
 
- Status (i.e helping with ones influence) 
 
- Knowledge (i.e sharing ones knowledge and teaching others)
 
- Physical efforts (helping with one’s body)
 

*2. Excellence in worshipping the Creator:*

This has two levels:

*- First level: *
 
 Mushāhadah : The level of Witnessing ("That you worship Allāh as if you see Him"), which is the higher of the two levels. 

* - Second level:*

 Murāqabah : The level of constant awareness and mindfulness of Allāh ("and if you do not see Him, [know that] He sees you")
 



*Evidence for Al-Iḥsān:*

Allāh Almighty says:#quran-block[إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ مَعَ ٱلَّذِينَ ٱتَّقَواْ وَّٱلَّذِينَ هُم مُّحۡسِنُونَ ١٢٨
][Indeed, Allāh is with those who fear Him and those who are doers of good.
(An-Naḥl Q16:128)]

